HEADWORD: Heugh
<hw>Heugh</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Hogh</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A crag; a cliff; a glen with
overhanging sides.</def> <mark>[Scot. & Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A shaft in a coal pit; a hollow in a quarry.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heuk</ent>⟦br⟧
